1. Overview
	* This tool is used to scan Java ctags files and generate dot file.
	Then use graphviz dot to get a class relationship diagram.
	* Only for testing, not stable.
	
1. Requirement
	* Windows XP
	* dot
		http://www.graphviz.org/Download.php
	* JDK 1.6
		http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html
	* Eclipse
		http://www.eclipse.org/
	* ANTLR & ANTLRWorks
		http://www.antlr.org/
	* Exuberant Ctags
		http://ctags.sourceforge.net/
		
2. Build
	* If you want to generate parser and lexer source files, run gen_antlr.bat.
	* Use eclipse to import the project path and compile it, or run compile.bat.
	
3. Test & Run
	* Put ctags.exe to this folder.
	* Put the Java source files to java_src. (Remove original files first)
	* Run run_gendot_java.bat, it will process the folder java_src,
	and generate the output file output.txt, out.dot and out.gif.
	* Open out.gif.

4. Test data
	* Test data is from Android 2.2 java source tree.
		http://www.android.com/

5. Bugs
	* This tool has many bugs to fix, mainly in SimpleJavaCtags.g

